<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="66" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/8–1947: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-05T18:00:00-04:00">September
                                    5, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>579. Careful consideration given by Dept <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 695 Aug 19<note n="1" xml:id="d66fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> India’s interest in membership TC. Prior firm
                            commitment to support Philippines for one of two vacancies precludes
                            U.S. support for second Asian member. You may in your discretion inform
                            GOI sense of foregoing. For your background, balance of colonial vs.
                            anti-colonial states would be disturbed by addition two Asian nations to
                            TC. Dept therefore favors neutral state for second vacancy.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>